HEADWORD: Depure
<hw>De*pure"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>d⟦eacute⟧purer</ets>. See <er>Depurate</er>.]</ety> <def>To
depurate; to purify.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>He shall first be <qex>depured</qex> and cleansed before that he
shall be laid up for pure gold in the treasures of God.</q> <rj><qau>Sir
T. More.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Depurgatory</ent>⟦br⟧
